  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed first floor side extension, by reason of its bulk and sitting would disrupt the sense of openness on this corner plot and represent a discordant feature, thereby generating harm upon the character and appearance of the application dwelling, the street scene and the Becontree Estate.&amp;nbsp; Furthermore,&amp;nbsp; the proposed development would generate an unneighbourly loss of outlook and increased overbearingness and overshadowing into neighbouring property No 74 Marlborough Road. The proposed development is therefore contrary to the following:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) (MHCLG, February 2019);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies D1, D4, D8, HC1 of The London Plan (March 2021);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies CP2 and CP3 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies BP8 and BP11 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies SP2, DMD1, DMD6 of&amp;nbsp;The London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation Version, October 2020);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Residential Extensions and Alterations (SPD) (February 2012)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed variation in roof heights would generate a disjointed and incongruous form to the uniformity of the existing dwellinghouse which is considered harmful to the character and appearance of the site and street scene and Becontree Estate. The proposal development is therefore contrary to the following:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) (MHCLG, February 2019);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies D1, D4, D8, HC1 of The London Plan (March 2021);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies CP2 and CP3 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policy BP11 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies SP2, DMD1, DMD6 of The London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation Version, October 2020);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Residential Extensions and Alterations (SPD) (February 2012)&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
